Sarkozy: France, Germany Want ‘New Treaty’

-- B y   M a r k   D e e n
-- 
2011-12-05T14:39:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-05/sarkozy-france-germany-want-new-treaty-.html
France and Germany want a new
European Union treaty to set out rules form euro area
governments, President  Nicolas Sarkozy  said after meeting with
 Chancellor Angela Merkel .  “We want it to be impossible for the deregulation that led
to the euro zone’s current situation to recurr any case, we want
a new treaty,” Sarkozy said in Paris. “Our preference is for a
treaty of 27 but we’re perfectly ready to have a treaty of 17.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Deen in Paris at 
